This repository contains prolog code to solve the Slither Link puzzle modeling
it as a Constraint Satisfaction Problem.
It is an assignment as a part of CS621 course on Artificial Intelligence

References (given on Moodle):
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slitherlink
http://diuflx71.unifr.ch/course/download/vorl08/uebungen/slitherlink.pdf
http://web.student.tuwien.ac.at/~e0225855/swiclpfd.pdf
http://www.sci.brooklyn.cuny.edu/~zhou/aspcompetition/
http://krazydad.com/slitherlink/

The code is written by 
Laxman Vemula
Vamsi Krishna
Savant Krishna "savant.2020@gmail.com"

Files:
1. slitherlink_program.pl: Contains the prolog code which will be used to solve the puzzle. This will be used by the python
2. slitherlink.py: Python script which takes the input file as argument and processes it and prints the solution on standard output.

How to execute:
./slitherlink.py <input-file>

Input file should be exactly in the format as discussed in the class.
Example:
6 6
2 3 3 2 1 3
2 -1 -1 -1 1 3
2 -1 -1 0 0 2
2 1 3 -1 -1 2
3 3 -1 -1 -1 3
2 2 2 3 2 3

